review_blob: Bottle. Aroma: big malt nose with caramel notes. No hop aroma.  overall sweet aroma.  even smells dark.  Appearance:  dark caramel color with a thick dense tan head.  good retention.  Taste: big malt without the huge sweetness youre expecting.  chocolate notes with lingering caramel.  finish is mildly dry. There is some spicy undertone in there.  Mouthfeel: slight carbonic bite.  after which is smooth with a full  mouth feel.  Overall:  great beer.  drink when time is on your side and sip and enjoy.
Medium hop nose with a light malt overtone .  citrusy hop flavor but not over done.  not an over the top hop beer.  medium body either medium carbonation.  good hoppy  beer.

Hoppy nose with malty undertones.  Being an American ipa, its focused on the the hops, but...  Its not too crazy.  Great flavor and bitterness.  While not the example for hop heads, it should be what american ipas should be.
Nice citus nose, balanced hop bitterness, great hop flavor.  Little malt to counter the hops.  Well balanced.
